1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of James
2 Thomas Clark.
3 WHEREAS, James Thomas Clark was born on June 9, 2007, to John and Necole
4 Darnall Clark of Fulton, Kentucky; and
5 WHEREAS, James Thomas Clark attended Hickman County schools and grew to
6 be a young man of many pursuits, but he particularly loved outdoor activities such as
7 archery and hunting. He always looked forward to hunting season when he could take
8 that trophy buck back to his family; and
9 WHEREAS, as a member of the Inside Out Archery club, which promotes target
10 archery, hunting, and conservation of natural resources, James Thomas Clark won both
11 state and national titles in the Scholastic 3-D Archery (S3DA) competitions; and
12 WHEREAS, James Thomas Clark was as passionate about his education as he was
13 about his outdoor pursuits. He excelled in math and science and was chosen to attend the
14 Gatton Academy of Mathematics and Science at Western Kentucky University; and
15 WHEREAS, for James Thomas Clark, spirituality remained a consistent force
16 throughout his life. He attended the Crosswind Church in Union City, Tennessee, and
17 served on the church worship team and participated in the church youth group; and
18 WHEREAS, James Thomas Clark departed this earth on September 20, 2024, at the
19 age of 17 years to an everlasting life in heaven, protected and loved by Jesus Christ our
20 eternal savior; and
21 WHEREAS, James Thomas Clark was preceded in death by his paternal
22 grandfather, Voris Clark; and
23 WHEREAS, James Thomas Clark is survived by his parents; his sister, Cora Clark;
24 his maternal grandparents, Clifton and Debra Darnall; his paternal grandmother, Linda
25 Wilson Clark; his aunts, Kim (Scott) Johnson and Rev. Angela Clark; and his cousin,
26 Preasley Yates;
27 NOW, THEREFORE,
